{
  "text": "Qualitative Data Analysis. Prior to the analysis of the data, normality test was carried out to find out whether the data were normally distributed and it was found that the values of skewness and kurtosis are p<+1.5 and p>-1.5 normal distribution. Both the skewness (-.43) and kurtosis (-.22) values of \"Views about the Effect on Student\" subscale and the skewness (-.02) and kurtois (-.27) values of the \"Views about the Effect on Courses and Teacher\" subscale are between +1,5 and -1,5. It is assumed that distribution is normal when the skewness and kurtosis values of the two subscales are between +1,5 and -1,5 [CITATION_1] . Therefore, the current study included independent t-test and one-way variance (ANOVA) analyzes that can be performed with normal distribution.",
